    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (77.06) and **Jackson Merrill** (74.85), who are our top-rated starters. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a favorable matchup against Alcantara, where a combination of wind conditions and a solid xwOBA projection provide the highest efficiency score on the roster. **Jackson Merrill** maintains a similar trajectory, buoyed by the aggressive leadoff spot and a strong platoon advantage against Taillon. Meanwhile, **Josh Lowe** (71.68) remains an essential start despite a moderate raw base; his elite sprint speed and the high-leverage potential against Fedde\u2014compounded by the pitcher's slow delivery\u2014make him a critical asset in our pursuit of stolen bases, which remains our primary scarcity concern for the 5x5 Roto standings.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the coaching staff today involved **Miguel Vargas**, who landed at 58.95. While he narrowly missed the starting lineup, he was sidelined in favor of the slightly more efficient **Josh Jung** (59.39) and the utility floor provided by **Marcell Ozuna** (60.22), whose matchup against Pallante offers a safer stability profile. We are also monitoring the status of our bench rotation closely, as the postponement of **Gunnar Henderson** and the lingering IL status of **Jordan Westburg** have tightened our available depth. \n\nRisk management remains a priority for the bottom half of the order. While **Jacob Wilson** (65.23) is positioned well to capitalize on a weak opposing arm, we are wary of **Drake Baldwin** (46.72), whose matchup against the elite Skubal (2.71 xERA) is our most significant statistical hurdle of the day. Despite the sub-50 score, **Drake Baldwin** remains in the lineup due to our current lack of viable alternatives, but he will be watched closely for any signs of struggle against high-velocity, low-ERA pitching. With the majority of the roster facing pitchers with xERAs above 4.00, we are positioned for a high-scoring output, provided our aggressive baserunners like **Josh Lowe** can exploit their respective platoon edges.",
